.. _syn-tools-snapshot:

snapshot
========

The Synapse ``snapshot`` tool can be used to freeze/resume service operations to allow system admins to generate a
transactionally consistent volume snapshot using 3rd party tools.

Syntax
------

``snapshot`` is executed using ``python -m synapse.tools.snapshot``. The command usage is as follows:

.. shell:: --fail-ok python -m synapse.tools.snapshot -h
